vf5hXhkgVuZ","label":"location"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recxiSg5QZWkj9Hy3","label":"location"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recpCMN0bRpzByjaR","label":"location"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recdx9jGjxLSDKDOw","label":"location"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"rec17BV2zJmVUdbIV","label":"location"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"recltAvLmGRfERhYp","label":"predecessor"},{"source":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","target":"rec4bAiAcAOo9mPwO","label":"part of"}],"verses":[{"id":"recumAtzkC7XajiMh","ref":"Acts.27.1","text":"And when it was determined that we should sail into Italy, they delivered Paul and certain other prisoners unto one named Julius, a centurion of Augustus’ band.","year":62},{"id":"receA9925uSi03unB","ref":"Acts.27.2","text":"And entering into a ship of Adramyttium, we launched, meaning to sail by the coasts of Asia; one Aristarchus, a Macedonian of Thessalonica, being with us.","year":62},{"id":"recgtz6lXHyRVLLCD","ref":"Acts.27.3","text":"And the next day we touched at Sidon. And Julius courteously entreated Paul, and gave him liberty to go unto his friends to refresh himself.","year":62},{"id":"recCt38amZPjV6A8l","ref":"Acts.27.4","text":"And when we had launched from thence, we sailed under Cyprus, because the winds were contrary.","year":62},{"id":"recfh8gJtrjOZ6a14","ref":"Acts.27.5","text":"And when we had sailed over the sea of Cilicia and Pamphylia, we came to Myra, a city of Lycia.","year":62},{"id":"rec430soQfJz7F4UX","ref":"Acts.27.6","text":"And there the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing into Italy; and he put us therein.","year":62},{"id":"recsXcjC95ZzYQ9E4","ref":"Acts.27.7","text":"And when we had sailed slowly many days, and scarce were come over against Cnidus, the wind not suffering us, we sailed under Crete, over against Salmone;","year":62},{"id":"recxrGYb9tcynKxNa","ref":"Acts.27.8","text":"And, hardly passing it, came unto a place which is called The fair havens; nigh whereunto was the city of Lasea.","year":62}]}
